1.title: Episode #2.1
1.plot: They may be back in Newcastle, but it's all change for Geordie Shore; Greg has left to find true love, Vicky and Sophie have pledged chastity to their new boyfriends, Gary promises Charlotte's Mum that he won't, Charlotte promises to do the ironing for a year if she does and James is nurturing a worldie-magnet comb-over. But with two new housemates ready to join the family, peace isn't set to last.

2.title: Episode #2.2
2.plot: Vicky and Ricci fall for each other, James struggles to neck on and Jay and Gary fight over Rebecca. But that's nothing when the house is rocked as Gary's nocturnal habits push Charlotte over the edge.

3.title: Episode #2.3
3.plot: There's no time for the house to mourn Charlotte's departure as Vicky and Ricci's nocturnal spooning is interrupted by an unexpected visitor. Rebecca and Jay are still flirting outrageously whilst Gary and James are quick to get their kit off. Sophie has her heart broken and Holly is left reeling as James has the night of his life.

4.title: Episode #2.4
4.plot: James continues his lucky streak with the ladies unlike unlucky in love Sophie who is played for a mug. Gary persuades Charlotte to return... but has she managed to get over him as she hoped? Rebecca lays her cards on the table with Jay, and Ricci and Vicky take things to the next level. After a big night out, Holly finally summons the courage to make a play for her man - but does she get what she wants?

5.title: Episode #2.5
5.plot: The 'cheer us all up' party ends in carnage as Charlotte tries to move on and the boys exchange blows. Vicky and Ricci make their relationship official with jaw dropping consequences.

6.title: Episode #2.6
6.plot: Disastrous consequences for Ricci and Gary rock the Geordie Shore house leaving Vicky and Charlotte stunned. Picking up the pieces, Sophie has a difficult decision to make whilst Charlotte learns Gaz's true feelings for her. With Jay and James about to have the night of their lives, the girls set off on a road trip tackling a colonic, Geordie Style, with it all ending in tears before bedtime. But Jay and James have other plans for bedtime.

7.title: Episode #2.7
7.plot: The honeymoon period is over as Vicky and Ricci split. Rebecca reveals her secret party trick, much to Jay's delight whilst Gary comes clean with Charlotte. Holly's Mum and Gaz' Dad make an appearance and the whole house falls out when the girl's jealous rage causes the boys to react. The house is at war once more.

8.title: Episode #2.8
8.plot: With only days to go until the end of the present series, hardly any relationships are left intact. Vicky and Ricci doggedly move on, Sophie gets dumped and Jay leaves an unpleasant taste in RebeccaÂ's mouth. But itÂ's not long before most of them have made up as only they know how.

9.title: Episode #2.9
9.plot: Newcastle's finest are back for a new series of Geordie Shore. This time they have a brand new house. Sophie, James and new lass Rebecca give you an access all areas tour of their brand new crib.

1.title: Episode #3.1
1.plot: It's time to swap the grey river Tyne for the crystal blue waters of Cancun, Mexico for the carnage of Spring break. Vicky and Ricci are loved up, whilst Jay is missing the love of his life.

2.title: Episode #3.2
2.plot: With the house reduced to carnage and Sophie losing even more faith in boyfriend Joel, there are still plenty of beaches to party on. Meanwhile Holly ups her game in pursuit of James.

3.title: Episode #3.3
3.plot: Sophie is elated as Joel surprises her with a visit. But will he be able to behave himself? And with everyone fearing that his worldie mission may now be over, Holly movies in on her prey.

4.title: Episode #3.4
4.plot: The chaos in Cancun continues as Gaz celebrates his birthday in true Geordie style. Charlotte takes her holiday romance to the next level. Vicky erupts as Cancun Chris gets sweet revenge.

5.title: Episode #3.5
5.plot: Vicky and Ricci return to the house in time for Becca's birthday which goes off in usual Geordie style. Sophie sends Joel back to England, but it's not long before she regrets the decision.

6.title: Episode #3.6
6.plot: An unexpected call means James has to choose between his best mates and Holly. Gary has another threesome and a night out trying to forget about Gary ends in disaster for Charlotte.

7.title: Episode #3.7
7.plot: The boy-girl divide returns. Charlotte and Gaz aren't speaking, Becca and Jay are continually arguing, Holly and James' nurse-patient relationship is back to strictly professional.

8.title: Episode #3.8
8.plot: It's the final few days of spring break and the house is rocked by the loss of yet another member. In the last hours, to the disbelief of everyone, Ricci plans his proposal to Vicky.

1.title: Episode #4.1
1.plot: After a fun filled summer in Cancun the Geordie Shore gang are back with a bang. With two new spaces in the house, it can only mean one thing, fresh meat for the family.

2.title: Episode #4.2
2.plot: The gang throw Ricci and Vicky an engagement party to remember. There'll be booze and banter aplenty, but it turns into a night that everyone will remember for all the wrong reasons.

3.title: Episode #4.3
3.plot: With Ricci and Sophie having been asked to leave the house, he rest of the Geordie Shore gang decide a road trip to Liverpool is in order to check out the clubs and talent.

4.title: Episode #4.4
4.plot: The Geordie Shore house is far from happy place with Vicky and Sophie still not talking and the rest of the house caught in divide - it's stormy seas ahead at the Shore.

5.title: Episode #4.5
5.plot: Peace has finally been restored in the house now that Vicky and Sophie have made up, but nothing lasts forever and when Ricci sees red on a family night out, disaster strikes.

6.title: Episode #4.6
6.plot: It's James' birthday and the gang plan a surprise trip to Dublin to celebrate with a secret guest, but on their return their is brought down by Ricci's return with some bad news.

7.title: Episode #4.7
7.plot: With Ricci gone from the Geordie Shore house, the rest of the gang are determined to keep Vicky's spirits up and the boys decide that what better way than a walk on the wild side - camping.

8.title: Episode #4.8
8.plot: It's all coming to an end in the house with some keener to leave than others. Before they pack their bags, there's time for a big bash, Geordie style, and it seems like love is all around.

1.title: Episode #5.1
1.plot: The Geordie Shore gang are back in a pimped up pad and ready to cause chaos once again.

2.title: Episode #5.2
2.plot: The gang return from Amsterdam and it's time to test Newcastle a new one. Vicky and Ricci celebrate breaking the Geordie Shore relationship curse and the gang try out speed dating.

3.title: Episode #5.3
3.plot: There's tension in the Toon, as James brings girlfriend Kate on a night out, leaving Holly unimpressed. The Geordie Shore house explodes as Vicky and Ricci have a row to remember.

4.title: Episode #5.4
4.plot: The Geordie Tour of Europe is back on as the gang are off to Prague for banter, birds and booze. The girls get their guns out at the shooting range whilst the boys visit the local strip clubs.

5.title: Episode #5.5
5.plot: The chaos continues as the gang return from Prague to a turbulent Toon. The house is in total meltdown as Charlotte and Gary finally come to blows, and it looks like it could be the end for Vicky and Ricci.

6.title: Episode #5.6
6.plot: Charlotte returns to the Geordie Shore house just in time to join the rest of the gang on a Geordie Tour of Barcelona. Our favourite Geordies battle in the Spanish sun, sex and sangria.

7.title: Episode #5.7
7.plot: The gang return from Barcelona with Charlotte's declaration of love for Gary still hanging in the air and Vicky set for a final showdown with Ricci.

8.title: Episode #5.8
8.plot: With the gang off after the biggest fight in the show's history, there's an icy atmosphere between the boys and the girls as they're off to the Alps for their final Geordie Tour.

1.title: Episode #6.1
1.plot: The Geordies return and they're heading Down Under to bring our Aussie cousins a little taste of Newcastle. Bish, Bosh, Bonza.

2.title: Episode #6.2
2.plot: The group are in high spirits as they get a surprise visit from Jay. Charlotte is still coming to terms with her feelings for Gaz. James' battle with Holly is set to continue.

3.title: Episode #6.3
3.plot: James and Gaz come to blows over pulling and Gaz is forced to leave the house. Vicky rashes on and Holly gets up close and personal with the one and only Scotty T.

4.title: Episode #6.4
4.plot: Whilst the fittest guy in Australia sends the girls into a spin, Scotty and Gaz square up as nightclubbing gets nasty. House destruction sees Gary head into the bush.

5.title: Episode #6.5
5.plot: An anger management session is arranged for the group, and Charlotte lets out all her negative feelings towards Gaz. Sophie and Joel get too drunk and embarrass the group on a night out.

6.title: Episode #6.6
6.plot: With Charlotte returning from the Bush a new woman, the housemates lay down the law for Scotty, slapping him with a drinking ban hoping that he will stop smashing up the house.

7.title: Episode #6.7
7.plot: James and Gary come to blows which sends shockwaves through the house and Charlotte's heart strings are pulled for Gary as she offers him support.

8.title: Episode #6.8
8.plot: As their time in Sydney comes to an end, the singles make it their mission to have a storming night in the Whitsundays. The coupled housemates have raised suspicions.

10.title: Episode #11.10
10.plot: The gang's Greek adventure comes to a dramatic end, there is a surprise arrival and Marnie has some massive news.

2.title: Episode #12.2
2.plot: Charlotte finally turns up with some bunnies and some bigger news for Gaz. Will Holly share her secret? Aaron and Scott's dates with Chantelle end badly as the lads and Chloe all kick off.

3.title: Episode #12.3
3.plot: Charlotte gets the girls to go hard on Gaz, Scott drops the girlfriend bomb on Chantelle and Holly has a big bust up with Charlotte when she sees her kissing Chloe.

7.plot: Marnie necks on with new lad Marty to teach Aaron a lesson. Charlotte's got Chloe's back when it all kicks off between the girls. Gary and Charlotte end up in bed causing ripples.
